-- Australian Open Champions to Get Record $2.1 Million Prize Money in 2011
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2010-10-05T00:26:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/australian-open-champions-to-get-record-2-1-million-prize-money-in-2011.html
The singles champions at next year’s
Australian Open will each pocket a record A$2.2 million ($2.1
million) in prize money.    Tennis Australia said today it increased the total prize
fund at the season-opening Grand Slam to A$25 million, up from
the A$24.1 million on offer at this year’s tournament.  Roger Federer  and Serena Williams  each won A$2.1 million
for taking the singles titles in Melbourne nine months ago.  Rafael Nadal  and Kim Clijsters  each earned $1.7 million for
their U.S. Open victories last month.            To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  